@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE, 0009)
' @id(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
' @ref(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
'
' Current-side domain anchor for the single deterministic render engine
' as built: mdd_core::RenderTree (the one tree enumeration) +
' Project::{render_sources,all_render_sources,rendered_mirror_path},
' driven by mdd_render::render_selection and the `mdd render` mdd-cli
' subcommand (Commands::Render). The /mdd-render skill is a thin wrapper.
'
' @desc(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE, "Built as: mdd_core::RenderTree { Models, CycleDiffs, OclConstraints, WholeMap, Deploy, ReviewDiff } with RenderTree::ALL the single tree list; Project::render_sources/all_render_sources enumerate it; Project::rendered_mirror_path is the deterministic source→.mdd/rendered/ mirror (review diffs kept in place). mdd_render::render_selection is the one engine; render_project/render_cycle_diffs/render_ocl_diagrams are thin wrappers over it. `mdd render` (mdd-cli Commands::Render) exposes it: no args = full set, --only <trees> or explicit paths = subset. The /mdd-render skill (templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL) only does fuzzy subset intake, diagnostic triage, and fix suggestions.")
title Render engine — domain (current)

class RenderEngine {
  + project : Project
  + renderedTrees : Set(Tree)
  + sources() : Set(SourceFile)
  + render(s : SourceFile) : RenderedFile
  + renderedPathOf(s : SourceFile) : Path
}

class Project {
  + enumeratedTrees : Set(Tree)
  + sourcesFor(t : Tree) : Set(SourceFile)
}

class SourceFile {
  + path : Path
  + tree : Tree
}

class RenderedFile {
  + path : Path
}

enum Tree {
  Models
  CycleDiffs
  OclConstraints
  WholeMap
  Deploy
  ReviewDiff
}

RenderEngine "1" o-- "1" Project : tree set (single source)
RenderEngine ..> SourceFile : enumerates via Project
RenderEngine ..> RenderedFile : writes mirror
SourceFile "1" --> "1" RenderedFile : deterministic mirror
Project --> Tree

note bottom of RenderEngine
  As built: render_selection consumes
  Project::all_render_sources (RenderTree::ALL) —
  one list, no skill-prose duplicate
  (OCL-RENDER-TREE-PARITY). rendered_mirror_path
  is the pure path mirror (OCL-RENDER-PATH-MIRROR).
end note
@enduml
